School Management System

Overview

The School Management System is a web-based application designed to streamline and automate school operations. It provides different user roles such as Super Admin, Branch Admin, and Teacher, allowing efficient management of school branches, student data, and teaching resources.

Features

Authentication System: Secure login/logout functionality.

Super Admin Dashboard: Manage multiple school branches and view system-wide reports.

Branch Admin Management: Oversee branch operations, including student and staff management.

Teacher Dashboard: Access to student data, class schedules, and progress tracking.

Database Integration: Efficient data storage and retrieval.

Installation

Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:

Python 3.8+

pip (Python package manager)

Setup

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/Gollasrikaran/school_management.git
cd school_management

Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the application:
streamlit run app.py

Project Structure
school_management/
│── app.py                  # Main application entry point
│── auth.py                 # Authentication module
│── branch_admin.py         # Branch admin functionalities
│── branchadmin_overview.py # Branch-level overview
│── database.py             # Database connectivity
│── superadmin_overview.py  # Super admin dashboard
│── teacher_dashboard.py    # Teacher functionalities
│── requirements.txt        # Project dependencies
│── README.md               # Project documentation
